* In [[Amn]] they were grown in the [[Purple Hills]] region.
* In [[Cormyr]], quince was grown in the farmlands along the kingdom's southern coast.{{Cite web/theedverse/2020-07-03 - Cormyr's Pick as you Walk Plants}}
* In the [[Moonsea]] region, the [[Bounty of the Goddess (Voonlar)|Bounty of the Goddess]] temple grew and sold quinces.{{Cite web/Elminster Speaks archive|9}}{{Cite web/Elminster Speaks/Part 7: The House of the Helm}}
* The [[Sword Coast]].<ref>
* In [[Tethyr]], they could be found growing as a crop or in the wild all across the nation.

document_data.Usages of Quinces:
* In the town of [[Fendarl's Gate]], it was often used to garnish thick slabs of [[bacon]].
* [[Purple Hills Cider]], a type of [[cider]] made with a variety of different fruits grown in the Purple Hills region, included quinces in its recipe.
* Quinces were an essential ingredient in the handfood [[quince stick]]s.<ref> Similarly, quince-and-crushed-insects sticks were handfoods from the [[Vilhon Reach]], [[Shaar]], [[Var]], and [[Estagund]].{{cite web| url = https://web.archive.org/web/20230716220132/http://www.candlekeep.com/library/articles/sse/sse_040506-07.htm| title = So Saith Ed Apr – Jun 2007| accessdate = 16-07-2023| date = 25-11-2021}}
* The [[elf|elven]] dish [[vaervren]] was sometimes seasoned with diced quince.{{Cite web/theedverse/2023-02-22 - Vaervren}}
* Quince preserves were a staple of a [[dwarf|dwarvish]] pantry.{{Cite dragon/278/Forge and Hammer|58}} Quince marmalades and butters were sold via ''[[Aurora's Whole Realms Catalogue]]''.
* Some believed that quince possessed medicinal properties that aided with various eye and skin [[disease]]s, as well as with dysentery.
